The paper focuses on optimizing clustering algorithms for modern non-uniform memory architectures (NUMA), which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the performance of parallel implementations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents an updated algorithm for Euclidean distance, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and physics (cs.PF).
